speciesData.name: Rowlet
speciesData.flavor_text:
Silently it glides, drawing near its targets. Before
they even notice it, it begins to pelt them with
vicious kicks.

speciesData.name: Dartrix
speciesData.flavor_text:
It throws sharp feathers called blade quills
at enemies or prey. It seldom misses.

speciesData.name: Decidueye
speciesData.flavor_text:
Although basically cool and cautious, when it’s
caught by surprise, it’s seized by panic.

speciesData.name: Litten
speciesData.flavor_text:
It doesn’t allow its emotions to be easily seen.
Earning its trust takes time. It prefers solitude.

speciesData.name: Torracat
speciesData.flavor_text:
It boasts powerful front legs. With a single
punch, it can bend an iron bar right over.

speciesData.name: Incineroar
speciesData.flavor_text:
After hurling ferocious punches and flinging
furious kicks, it finishes opponents off by
spewing fire from around its navel.

speciesData.name: Popplio
speciesData.flavor_text:
This Pokémon can control water bubbles. It
practices diligently so it can learn to make
big bubbles.

speciesData.name: Brionne
speciesData.flavor_text:
It cares deeply for its companions. When its
Trainer is feeling down, it performs a cheery
dance to try and help.

speciesData.name: Primarina
speciesData.flavor_text:
Its singing voice is its chief weapon in battle.
This Pokémon’s Trainer must prioritize the daily
maintenance of its throat at all costs.

speciesData.name: Pikipek
speciesData.flavor_text:
This Pokémon feeds on berries, whose leftover
seeds become the ammunition for the attacks it
fires off from its mouth.

speciesData.name: Trumbeak
speciesData.flavor_text:
By bending its beak, it can produce a variety of
calls and brand itself a noisy nuisance for
its neighbors.

speciesData.name: Toucannon
speciesData.flavor_text:
Within its beak, its internal gas ignites,
explosively launching seeds with enough power
to pulverize boulders.

speciesData.name: Yungoos
speciesData.flavor_text:
It wanders around in a never-ending search for
food. At dusk, it collapses from exhaustion and
falls asleep on the spot.

speciesData.name: Gumshoos
speciesData.flavor_text:
It adores having Rattata and Raticate for dinner,
but as it’s diurnal, it never encounters them.
This Pokémon boasts incredible patience.

speciesData.name: Grubbin
speciesData.flavor_text:
They often gather near places frequented by
electric Pokémon in order to avoid being
attacked by bird Pokémon.

speciesData.name: Charjabug
speciesData.flavor_text:
From the food it digests, it generates electricity,
and it stores this energy in its electric sac.

speciesData.name: Vikavolt
speciesData.flavor_text:
It produces electricity via an electrical organ in
its abdomen. It overwhelms bird Pokémon with
shocking beams of electrical energy.

speciesData.name: Crabrawler
speciesData.flavor_text:
It punches so much, its pincers often come off
from overuse, but they grow back quickly. What
little meat they contain is rich and delicious.

speciesData.name: Crabominable
speciesData.flavor_text:
It just throws punches indiscriminately. In times
of desperation, it can lop off its own pincers
and fire them like rockets.

speciesData.name: Oricorio
speciesData.flavor_text:
This Oricorio has sipped red nectar. Its
passionate dance moves cause its enemies
to combust in both body and mind.

speciesData.name: Cutiefly
speciesData.flavor_text:
Myriads of Cutiefly flutter above the heads of
people who have auras resembling those
of flowers.

speciesData.name: Ribombee
speciesData.flavor_text:
Some of Ribombee’s pollen puffs are highly
nutritious. They are sometimes sold
as supplements.

speciesData.name: Rockruff
speciesData.flavor_text:
This Pokémon has lived with people since times
long ago. It can sense when its Trainer is in the
dumps and will stick close by its Trainer’s side.

speciesData.name: Lycanroc
speciesData.flavor_text:
When properly raised from a young age, it will
become a trustworthy partner that will
absolutely never betray its Trainer.

speciesData.name: Wishiwashi
speciesData.flavor_text:
It’s awfully weak and notably tasty, so everyone
is always out to get it. As it happens, anyone
trying to bully it receives a painful lesson.

speciesData.name: Mareanie
speciesData.flavor_text:
It’s found crawling on beaches and seafloors.
The coral that grows on Corsola’s head is as
good as a five-star banquet to this Pokémon.

speciesData.name: Toxapex
speciesData.flavor_text:
Those attacked by Toxapex’s poison will suffer
intense pain for three days and three nights.
Post-recovery, there will be some aftereffects.

speciesData.name: Mudbray
speciesData.flavor_text:
It has a stubborn, individualistic disposition.
Eating dirt, making mud, and playing in the mire
all form part of its daily routine.

speciesData.name: Mudsdale
speciesData.flavor_text:
Its heavy, mud-covered kicks are its best
means of attack, and it can reduce large trucks
to scrap without breaking a sweat.

speciesData.name: Dewpider
speciesData.flavor_text:
When it comes across enemies or potential prey,
this Pokémon smashes its
water-bubble-covered head into them.

speciesData.name: Araquanid
Fomantis
speciesData.flavor_text:
They give off a sweet and refreshing scent.
Cutiefly often gather near the tall grass where
Fomantis are hiding.

speciesData.name: Lurantis
speciesData.flavor_text:
It fires beams from its sickle-shaped petals.
These beams are powerful enough to cleave
through thick metal plates.

speciesData.name: Morelull
speciesData.flavor_text:
As it drowses the day away, it nourishes itself
by sucking from tree roots. It wakens at the fall
of night, wandering off in search of a new tree.

speciesData.name: Shiinotic
speciesData.flavor_text:
It emits flickering spores that cause drowsiness.
When its prey succumb to sleep, this Pokémon
feeds on them by sucking in their energy.

speciesData.name: Salandit
speciesData.flavor_text:
Volcanoes or dry, craggy places are its home.
It emanates a sweet-smelling poisonous gas
that attracts bug Pokémon, then attacks them.

speciesData.name: Salazzle
speciesData.flavor_text:
Filled with pheromones, its poisonous gas can
be diluted to use in the production of
luscious perfumes.

speciesData.name: Stufful
speciesData.flavor_text:
A touch from anyone except a known friend
sends it into a surging frenzy. It’s an incredibly
dangerous Pokémon.

speciesData.name: Bewear
speciesData.flavor_text:
This Pokémon has the habit of hugging its
companions. Many Trainers have left this world
after their spines were squashed by its hug.

speciesData.name: Bounsweet
speciesData.flavor_text:
Although it’s too sugary for human consumption,
Bounsweet’s sweat can be watered down into a
juice with just the right amount of sweetness.

speciesData.name: Steenee
speciesData.flavor_text:
This Pokémon is always bouncing around
energetically. Other Pokémon are attracted by
its lively appearance and pleasant aroma.

speciesData.name: Tsareena
speciesData.flavor_text:
A Pokémon known for the beauty of its
well-shaped legs, it sometimes appears as a
mascot in advertisements for beauty salons.

speciesData.name: Comfey
speciesData.flavor_text:
Baths prepared with the flowers from its vine
have a relaxing effect, so this Pokémon
is a hit with many people.

speciesData.name: Oranguru
speciesData.flavor_text:
Deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy, this
Pokémon abides. On rare occasions, it shows up
at the beach to match wits with Slowking.

speciesData.name: Passimian
speciesData.flavor_text:
They battle with hard berries for weapons.
Their techniques are passed from the boss to
the group, generation upon generation.

speciesData.name: Wimpod
speciesData.flavor_text:
Its habitat varies from beaches to seabeds.
A natural scavenger, it will gleefully chow down
on anything edible, no matter how rotten.

speciesData.name: Golisopod
speciesData.flavor_text:
It battles skillfully with its six arms, but spends
most of its time peacefully meditating in caves
deep beneath the sea.

speciesData.name: Sandygast
speciesData.flavor_text:
It takes control of anyone who puts a hand in its
mouth. And so it adds to the accumulation of
its sand-mound body.

speciesData.name: Palossand
speciesData.flavor_text:
Buried beneath the castle are masses of
dried-up bones from those whose vitality
it has drained.

speciesData.name: Pyukumuku
speciesData.flavor_text:
These Pokémon line the beaches. The sticky
mucous that covers their bodies can be used to
soothe sunburned skin. How convenient!

speciesData.name: Type: Null
speciesData.flavor_text:
Due to the danger that this synthetic Pokémon
may go on a rampage, it wears a control mask
to restrain its power.

speciesData.name: Silvally
speciesData.flavor_text:
Although its name was Type: Null at first, the
boy who evolved it into this form gave it the
name by which it is now known.

speciesData.name: Minior
speciesData.flavor_text:
Strong impacts can knock it out of its shell. This
Pokémon was born from mutated nanoparticles.

speciesData.name: Komala
speciesData.flavor_text:
The log it holds was given to it by its parents at
birth. It has also been known to cling to the arm
of a friendly Trainer.

speciesData.name: Turtonator
speciesData.flavor_text:
It gushes fire and poisonous gases from its
nostrils. Its dung is an explosive substance and
can be put to various uses.

speciesData.name: Togedemaru
speciesData.flavor_text:
The long hairs on its back act as lightning rods.
The bolts of lightning it attracts are stored as
energy in its electric sac.

speciesData.name: Mimikyu
speciesData.flavor_text:
A lonely Pokémon, it conceals its terrifying
appearance beneath an old rag so it can get
closer to people and other Pokémon.

speciesData.name: Bruxish
speciesData.flavor_text:
It stuns its prey with psychokinesis and then
grinds them to mush with its strong teeth.
Even Shellder’s shell is no match for it.

speciesData.name: Drampa
speciesData.flavor_text:
This Pokémon is friendly to people and loves
children most of all. It comes from deep in the
mountains to play with children it likes in town.

speciesData.name: Dhelmise
speciesData.flavor_text:
The soul of seaweed adrift in the waves became
reborn as this Pokémon. It maintains itself with
new infusions of seabed detritus and seaweed.

speciesData.name: Jangmo-o
speciesData.flavor_text:
They live in mountains where no trace of
humans can be detected. Jangmo-o grow
little by little as they battle one another.

speciesData.name: Hakamo-o
speciesData.flavor_text:
It sheds and regrows its scales on a continuous
basis. The scales become harder and sharper
each time they’re regrown.

speciesData.name: Kommo-o
speciesData.flavor_text:
Its rigid scales function as offense and defense.
In the past, its scales were processed and used
to make weapons and other commodities.

speciesData.name: Tapu Koko
speciesData.flavor_text:
It confuses its enemies by flying too quickly for
the eye to follow. It has a hair-trigger temper
but forgets what made it angry an instant later.

speciesData.name: Tapu Lele
speciesData.flavor_text:
As it flutters about, it scatters its strangely
glowing scales. Touching them is said to restore
good health on the spot.

speciesData.name: Tapu Bulu
speciesData.flavor_text:
The guardian deity of Ula’ula is a lazy Pokémon.
It commands plants to immobilize its foes and
then deals them a savage blow with its horns.

speciesData.name: Tapu Fini
speciesData.flavor_text:
The guardian deity of Poni, it can control water.
People say it can create pure water that will
wash away any uncleanness.

speciesData.name: Cosmog
speciesData.flavor_text:
In ages past, it was called the child of the stars.
It’s said to be a Pokémon from another world,
but no specific details are known.

speciesData.name: Cosmoem
speciesData.flavor_text:
There’s something accumulating around the
black core within its hard shell. People think
this Pokémon may come from another world.

speciesData.name: Solgaleo
speciesData.flavor_text:
This Pokémon is said to be a male evolution of
Cosmog. At the activation of its third eye, it
departs for another world.

speciesData.name: Lunala
speciesData.flavor_text:
Said to live in another world, this Pokémon
devours light, drawing the moonless dark veil of
night over the brightness of day.

speciesData.name: Nihilego
speciesData.flavor_text:
One of the Ultra Beasts. It’s unclear whether or
not this Pokémon is sentient, but sometimes it
can be observed behaving like a young girl.

speciesData.name: Buzzwole
speciesData.flavor_text:
A mysterious life-form called an Ultra Beast.
Witnesses saw it pulverize a dump truck with a
single punch.

speciesData.name: Pheromosa
speciesData.flavor_text:
One of the Ultra Beasts. It refuses to touch
anything, perhaps because it senses some
uncleanness in this world.

speciesData.name: Xurkitree
speciesData.flavor_text:
It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. It raided a
power plant, so people think it energizes itself
with electricity.

speciesData.name: Celesteela
speciesData.flavor_text:
One kind of Ultra Beast. Witnesses have seen it
burn down a forest by expelling gas from its
two arms.

speciesData.name: Kartana
speciesData.flavor_text:
One of the Ultra Beast life-forms, it was
observed cutting down a gigantic steel tower
with one stroke of its blade.

speciesData.name: Guzzlord
speciesData.flavor_text:
A dangerous Ultra Beast, it appears to be eating
constantly, but for some reason its droppings
have never been found.

speciesData.name: Necrozma
speciesData.flavor_text:
Light is apparently the source of its energy.
It has an extraordinarily vicious disposition
and is constantly firing off laser beams.

speciesData.name: Magearna
speciesData.flavor_text:
Its mechanized body is merely a vessel. Its true
self is its Soul-Heart, an artificial soul.

speciesData.name: Marshadow
speciesData.flavor_text:
It lurks in the shadows of others, copying their
movements and powers. This Pokémon is craven
and cowering.
